        "comment": {
            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13383935/comment/17363615",
                    "id": "17363615",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Krisztian Szucs",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Budapest"
                    },
                    "body": "We cannot use the {{git describe}} command with this workflow since it calculates the distance since the last tag reachable from the current commit. \r\n\r\nAn alternative could be to manually calculate the distance from the merge-base of the current commit and the latest tag where the latest should be defined by {{setup.py::default_version}} variable which we periodically bump after each release.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Krisztian Szucs",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Budapest"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-06-15T12:49:38.666+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-06-15T12:49:38.666+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13383935/comment/17364380",
                    "id": "17364380",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Krisztian Szucs",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Budapest"
                    },
                    "body": "{{setuptools_scm}}'s API only allows us to pass a git describe command, but git describe won't reach the new tags from the master branch since they are placed on release branches which diverge from master. We could calculate a version number ourselves but vendoring internal code from {{setuptools_scm}} is questionable.\r\n\r\nAnother approach could be to merge (not rebase) the release branches to the master branch so git describe can reach the tags.\r\n\r\ncc [~apitrou]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Krisztian Szucs",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Budapest"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-06-16T16:57:44.593+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-06-16T16:57:44.593+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13383935/comment/17364878",
                    "id": "17364878",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "What we do in pandas is directly after branching adding a tag on master with \"next.dev\" version. So eg when branching 3.x, we tag master with 4.0.0.dev. The versions based on git describe should work fine.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-06-17T11:14:42.120+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-06-17T11:14:42.120+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13383935/comment/17364924",
                    "id": "17364924",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Krisztian Szucs",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Budapest"
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the suggestion [~jorisvandenbossche], that's a nice workaround! The question is, shall we tag the fork point or the [commit where we bump|https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/aa28470ca2a901a80e88874b4341905a3188186f#diff-eb8b42d9346d0a5d371facf21a8bfa2d16fb49e213ae7c21f03863accebe0fcf] the development versions? There are intermediate commits.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kszucs",
                        "name": "kszucs",
                        "key": "kszucs",
                        "avatarUrls": {
